    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "I&#39;m late to this party, but @RicardoAltamirano is a bit mistaken.  The <code>endIndex</code> (second parameter) of <code>String.substring(int, int)</code> is an <b>exclusive</b> index, and it <i>won&#39;t</i> throw an exception for <code>index + 1</code> as long as <code>index &lt; length()</code> -- which is true even for the last character in the string."
  } ],
